HEADWORD: Sleeveless
<hw>Sleeve"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>sl⟦emac⟧fle⟦aacute⟧s</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having no
sleeves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lacking a cover, pretext, or palliation;
unreasonable; profitless; bootless; useless.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The vexation of a <qex>sleeveless</qex> errand.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Warburton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sleid</ent>⟦br⟧
